#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:429
msgid "OpenModelica Notebook Commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:431
msgid ""
"OMNotebook currently supports the commands and concepts that are "
"described in this section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:435
msgid "Cells"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:437
msgid ""
"Everything inside an OMNotebook document is made out of cells. A cell "
"basically contains a chunk of data. That data can be text, images, or "
"other cells. OMNotebook has four types of cells: headercell, textcell, "
"inputcell, and groupcell. Cells are ordered in a tree structure, where "
"one cell can be a parent to one or more additional cells. A tree view is "
"available close to the right border in the notebook window to display the"
" relation between the cells."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:450 ../../source/omnotebook.rst:677
msgid "*Textcell* – This cell type is used to display ordinary text and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:446
msgid ""
"images. Each textcell has a style that specifies how text is displayed. "
"The cell´s style can be changed in the menu Format->Styles, example of "
"different styles are: Text, Title, and Subtitle. The Textcell type also "
"has support for following links to other notebook documents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:460
msgid "*Inputcell* – This cell type has support for syntax highlighting and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:453
msgid ""
"evaluation. It is intended to be used for writing program code, e.g. "
"Modelica code. Evaluation is done by pressing the key combination "
"Shift+Return or Shift+Enter. All the text in the cell is sent to OMC "
"(OpenModelica Compiler/interpreter), where the text is evaluated and the "
"result is displayed below the inputcell. By double-clicking on the cell "
"marker in the tree view, the inputcell can be collapsed causing the "
"result to be hidden."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:471
msgid "*Latexcell* – This cell type has support for evaluation of latex scripts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:463
msgid ""
"It is intended to be mainly used for writing mathematical equations and "
"formulas for advanced documentation in OMNotebook. Each Latexcell "
"supports a maximum of one page document output.To evaluate this cell, "
"latex must be installed in your system.The users can copy and paste the "
"latex scripts and start the evaluation.Evaluation is done by pressing the"
" key combination Shift+Return or Shift+Enter or the green color eval "
"button present in the toolbar. The script in the cell is sent to latex "
"compiler, where it is evaluated and the output is displayed hiding the "
"latex source. By double-clicking on the cell marker in the tree view,the "
"latex source is displayed for further modification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:480
msgid "*Groupcell* – This cell type is used to group together other cell. A"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:474
msgid ""
"groupcell can be opened or closed. When a groupcell is opened all the "
"cells inside the groupcell are visible, but when the groupcell is closed "
"only the first cell inside the groupcell is visible. The state of the "
"groupcell is changed by the user double-clicking on the cell marker in "
"the tree view. When the groupcell is closed the marker is changed and the"
" marker has an arrow at the bottom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:483
msgid "Cursors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:485
msgid ""
"An OMNotebook document contains cells which in turn contain text. Thus, "
"two kinds of cursors are needed for positioning, text cursor and cell "
"cursor:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:491
msgid "*Textcursor* – A cursor between characters in a cell, appearing as a"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:490
msgid ""
"small vertical line. Position the cursor by clicking on the text or using"
" the arrow buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:504
msgid "*Cellcursor* – This cursor shows which cell currently has the input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:494
msgid ""
"focus. It consists of two parts. The main cellcursor is basically just a "
"thin black horizontal line below the cell with input focus. The "
"cellcursor is positioned by clicking on a cell, clicking between cells, "
"or using the menu item Cell->Next Cell or Cell->Previous Cell. The cursor"
" can also be moved with the key combination Ctrl+Up or Ctrl+Down. The "
"dynamic cellcursor is a short blinking horizontal line. To make this "
"visible, you must click once more on the main cellcursor (the long "
"horizontal line). NOTE: In order to paste cells at the cellcursor, the "
"*dynamic cellcursor must be made active* by clicking on the main "
"cellcursor (the horizontal line)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:507
msgid "Selection of Text or Cells"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:509
msgid ""
"To perform operations on text or cells we often need to select a range of"
" characters or cells."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:516
msgid "*Select characters* – There are several ways of selecting characters,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:513
msgid ""
"e.g. double-clicking on a word, clicking and dragging the mouse, or click"
" followed by a shift-click at an adjacent positioin selects the text "
"between the previous click and the position of the most recent shift-"
"click."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:524
msgid "*Select cells* – Cells can be selected by clicking on them. Holding"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:519
msgid ""
"down Ctrl and clicking on the cell markers in the tree view allows "
"several cells to be selected, one at a time. Several cells can be "
"selected at once in the tree view by holding down the Shift key. Holding "
"down Shift selects all cells between last selected cell and the cell "
"clicked on. This only works if both cells belong to the same groupcell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:527
msgid "File Menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:529
msgid "The following file related operations are available in the file menu:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:533
msgid "*Create a new noteboo*\\ k – A new notebook can be created using the"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:532
msgid ""
"menu File->New or the key combination Ctrl+N. A new document window will "
"then open, with a new document inside."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:541
msgid "*Open a notebook* – To open a notebook use File->Open in the menu or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:536
msgid ""
"the key combination Ctrl+O. Only files of the type .onb or .nb can be "
"opened. If a file does not follow the OMNotebook format or the FullForm "
"Mathematica Notebook format, a message box is displayed telling the user "
"what is wrong. Mathematica Notebooks must be converted to fullform before"
" they can be opened in OMNotebook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:549
msgid "*Save a notebook* – To save a notebook use the menu item File->Save"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:544
msgid ""
"or File->Save As. If the notebook has not been saved before the save as "
"dialog is shown and a filename can be selected. OMNotebook can only save "
"in xml format and the saved file is not compatible with Mathematica. Key "
"combination for save is Ctrl+S and for save as Ctrl+Shift+S. The saved "
"file by default obtains the file extension .onb."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:554
msgid "*Print* – Printing a document to a printer is done by pressing the"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:552
msgid ""
"key combination Ctrl+P or using the menu item File->Print. A normal print"
" dialog is displayed where the usually properties can be changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:559
msgid "*Import old document* – Old documents, saved with the old version of"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:557
msgid ""
"OMNotebook where a different file format was used, can be opened using "
"the menu item File->Import->Old OMNotebook file. Old documents have the "
"extension .xml."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:566
msgid "*Export text* – The text inside a document can be exported to a text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:562
msgid ""
"document. The text is exported to this document without almost any "
"structure saved. The only structure that is saved is the cell structure. "
"Each paragraph in the text document will contain text from one cell. To "
"use the export function, use menu item File->Export->Pure Text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:571
msgid "*Close a notebook window* – A notebook window can be closed using the"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:569
msgid ""
"menu item File->Close or the key combination Ctrl+F4. Any unsaved changes"
" in the document are lost when the notebook window is closed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:578
msgid "*Quitting OMNotebook* – To quit OMNotebook, use menu item File->Quit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:574
msgid ""
"or the key combination Crtl+Q. This closes all notebook windows; users "
"will have the option of closing OMC also. OMC will not automatically "
"shutdown because other programs may still use it. Evaluating the command "
"quit() has the same result as exiting OMNotebook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:581
msgid "Edit Menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:590
msgid "*Editing cell text* – Cells have a set of of basic editing functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:584
msgid ""
"The key combination for these are: Undo (Ctrl+Z), Redo (Ctrl+Y), Cut "
"(Ctrl+X), Copy (Ctrl+C) and Paste (Ctrl+V). These functions can also be "
"accessed from the edit menu; Undo (Edit->Undo), Redo (Edit->Redo), Cut "
"(Edit->Cut), Copy (Edit->Copy) and Paste (Edit->Paste). Selection of text"
" is done in the usual way by double-clicking, triple-clicking (select a "
"paragraph), dragging the mouse, or using (Ctrl+A) to select all text "
"within the cell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:595
msgid "*Cut cell* – Cells can be cut from a document with the menu item"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:593
msgid ""
"Edit->Cut or the key combination Ctrl+X. The cut function will always cut"
" cells if cells have been selected in the tree view, otherwise the cut "
"function cuts text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:600
msgid "*Copy cell* – Cells can be copied from a document with the menu item"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:598
msgid ""
"Edit->Copy or the key combination Ctrl+C. The copy function will always "
"copy cells if cells have been selected in the tree view, otherwise the "
"copy function copy text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:612
msgid "*Paste cell* – To paste copied or cut cells the cell cursor must be"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:603
msgid ""
"selected in the location where the cells should be pasted. This is done "
"by clicking on the cell cursor. Pasteing cells is done from the menu "
"Edit->Paste or the key combination Ctrl+V. If the cell cursor is selected"
" the paste function will always paste cells. OMNotebook share the same "
"application-wide clipboard. Therefore cells that have been copied from "
"one document can be pasted into another document. Only pointers to the "
"copied or cut cells are added to the clipboard, thus the cell that should"
" be pasted must still exist. Consequently a cell can not be pasted from a"
" document that has been closed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:616
msgid "*Find* – Find text string in the current notebook, with the options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:615
msgid ""
"match full word, match cell, search within closed cells. Short command "
"Ctrl+F."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:620
msgid "*Replace –* Find and replace text string in the current notebook,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:619
msgid ""
"with the options match full word, match cell, search+replace within "
"closed cells. Short command Ctrl+H."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:626
msgid "*View expression* – Text in a cell is stored internally as a subset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:623
msgid ""
"of HTML code and the menu item Edit->View Expression let the user switch "
"between viewing the text or the internal HTML representation. Changes "
"made to the HTML code will affect how the text is displayed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:629
msgid "Cell Menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:634
msgid "*Add textcell* – A new textcell is added with the menu item Cell->Add"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:632
msgid ""
"Cell (previous cell style) or the key combination Alt+Enter. The new "
"textcell gets the same style as the previous selected cell had."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:637
msgid "*Add inputcell* – A new inputcell is added with the menu item"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:637
msgid "Cell->Add Inputcell or the key combination Ctrl+Shift+I."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:640
msgid "*Add latexcell* – A new latexcell is added with the menu item"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:640
msgid "Cell->Add Latexcell or the key combination Ctrl+Shift+E."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:644
msgid "*Add groupcell* – A new groupcell is inserted with the menu item"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:643
msgid ""
"Cell->Groupcell or the key combination Ctrl+Shift+G. The selected cell "
"will then become the first cell inside the groupcell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:649
msgid "*Ungroup groupcell* – A groupcell can be ungrouped by selecting it in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:647
msgid ""
"the tree view and using the menu item Cell->Ungroup Groupcell or by using"
" the key combination Ctrl+Shift+U. Only one groupcell at a time can be "
"ungrouped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:653
msgid "*Split cell* – Spliting a cell is done with the menu item Cell->Split"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:652
msgid ""
"cell or the key combination Ctrl+Shift+P. The cell is splited at the "
"position of the text cursor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:660
msgid "*Delete cell* – The menu item Cell->Delete Cell will delete all cells"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:656
msgid ""
"that have been selected in the tree view. If no cell is selected this "
"action will delete the cell that have been selected by the cellcursor. "
"This action can also be called with the key combination Ctrl+Shift+D or "
"the key Del (only works when cells have been selected in the tree view)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:667
msgid "*Cellcursor* – This cell type is a special type that shows which cell"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:663
msgid ""
"that currently has the focus. The cell is basically just a thin black "
"line. The cellcursor is moved by clicking on a cell or using the menu "
"item Cell->Next Cell or Cell->Previous Cell. The cursor can also be moved"
" with the key combination Ctrl+Up or Ctrl+Down."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:670
msgid "Format Menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:673
msgid ""
"images. Each textcell has a style that specifies how text is displayed. "
"The cells style can be changed in the menu Format->Styles, examples of "
"different styles are: Text, Title, and Subtitle. The Textcell type also "
"have support for following links to other notebook documents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:687
msgid "*Text manipulation* – There are a number of different text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:680
msgid ""
"manipulations that can be done to change the appearance of the text. "
"These manipulations include operations like: changing font, changing "
"color and make text bold, but also operations like: changing the "
"alignment of the text and the margin inside the cell. All text "
"manipulations inside a cell can be done on single letters, words or the "
"entire text. Text settings are found in the Format menu. The following "
"text manipulations are available in OMNotebook:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:689
msgid "> Font family"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:691
msgid "> Font face (Plain, Bold, Italic, Underline)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:693
msgid "> Font size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:695
msgid "> Font stretch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:697
msgid "> Font color"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:699
msgid "> Text horizontal alignment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:701
msgid "> Text vertical alignment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:703
msgid "> Border thickness"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:705
msgid "> Margin (outside the border)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:707
msgid "> Padding (inside the border)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:710
msgid "Insert Menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:718
msgid "*Insert image* – Images are added to a document with the menu item"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:713
msgid ""
"Insert->Image or the key combination Ctrl+Shift+M. After an image has "
"been selected a dialog appears, where the size of the image can be "
"chosen. The images actual size is the default value of the image. "
"OMNotebook stretches the image accordantly to the selected size. All "
"images are saved in the same file as the rest of the document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:729
msgid "*Insert link* – A document can contain links to other OMNotebook file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:721
msgid ""
"or Mathematica notebook and to add a new link a piece of text must first "
"be selected. The selected text make up the part of the link that the user"
" can click on. Inserting a link is done from the menu Insert->Link or "
"with the key combination Ctrl+Shift+L. A dialog window, much like the one"
" used to open documents, allows the user to choose the file that the link"
" refers to. All links are saved in the document with a relative file path"
" so documents that belong together easily can be moved from one place to "
"another without the links failing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:732
msgid "Window Menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:738
msgid "*Change window* – Each opened document has its own document window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:735
msgid ""
"To switch between those use the Window menu. The window menu lists all "
"titles of the open documents, in the same order as they were opened. To "
"switch to another document, simple click on the title of that document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:741
msgid "Help Menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:744
msgid "*About OMNotebook* – Accessing the about message box for OMNotebook"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:744
msgid "is done from the menu Help->About OMNotebook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:747
msgid "*About Qt* – To access the message box for Qt, use the menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:747
msgid "Help->About Qt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:752
msgid "*Help Text* – Opening the help text (document OMNotebookHelp.onb) for"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:750
msgid ""
"OMNotebook can be done in the same way as any OMNotebook document is "
"opened or with the menu Help->Help Text. The menu item can also be "
"triggered with the key F1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:755
msgid "Additional Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:758
msgid "*Links* – By clicking on a link, OMNotebook will open the document"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:758
msgid "that is referred to in the link."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:765
msgid "*Update link* – All links are stored with relative file path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:761
msgid ""
"Therefore OMNotebook has functions that automatically updating links if a"
" document is resaved in another folder. Every time a document is saved, "
"OMNotebook checks if the document is saved in the same folder as last "
"time. If the folder has changed, the links are updated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:771
msgid "\\ *Evaluate whole Notebook* – All the cells present in the Notebook can"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:768
msgid ""
"be evaluated in one step by pressing the red color evalall button in the "
"toolbar. The cells are evaluated in the same order as they are in the "
"Notebook.However the latexcells cannot be evaluated by this feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:778
msgid "\\ *Evaluate several cells* – Several inputcells can be evaluated at"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:774
msgid ""
"the same time by selecting them in the treeview and then pressing the key"
" combination Shift+Enter or Shift+Return. The cells are evaluated in the "
"same order as they have been selected. If a groupcell is selected all "
"inputcells in that groupcell are evaluated, in the order they are located"
" in the groupcell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:791
msgid ""
"\\ *Moving and Reordering cells in a Notebook* – It is possible to shift "
"cells"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:781
msgid ""
"to a new position and change the hierarchical order of the document.This "
"can be done by clicking the cell and press the Up and Down arrow button "
"in the tool bar to move either Up or Down. The cells are moved one cell "
"above or below.It is also possible to move a cell directly to a new "
"position with one single click by pressing the red color bidirectional "
"UpDown arrow button in the toolbar. To do this the user has to place the "
"cell cursor to a position where the selected cells must be moved. After "
"selecting the cell cursor position, select the cells you want to shift "
"and press the bidirectional UpDown arrow button. The cells are shifted in"
" the same order as they are selected.This is especially very useful when "
"shifting a group cell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:810
msgid "*Command completion* – Inputcells have command completion support,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:794
msgid ""
"which checks if the user is typing a command (or any keyword defined in "
"the file commands.xml) and finish the command. If the user types the "
"first two or three letters in a command, the command completion function "
"fills in the rest. To use command completion, press the key combination "
"Ctrl+Space or Shift+Tab. The first command that matches the letters "
"written will then appear. Holding down Shift and pressing Tab "
"(alternative holding down Ctrl and pressing Space) again will display the"
" second command that matches. Repeated request to use command completion "
"will loop through all commands that match the letters written. When a "
"command is displayed by the command completion functionality any field "
"inside the command that should be edited by the user is automatically "
"selected. Some commands can have several of these fields and by pressing "
"the key combination Ctrl+Tab, the next field will be selected inside the "
"command. > Active Command completion: Ctrl+Space / Shift+Tab > Next "
"command: Ctrl+Space / Shift+Tab > Next field in command: Ctrl+Tab’"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:816
msgid "*Generated plot* – When plotting a simulation result, OMC uses the"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:813
msgid ""
"program Ptplot to create a plot. From Ptplot OMNotebook gets an image of "
"the plot and automatically adds that image to the output part of an "
"inputcell. Like all other images in a document, the plot is saved in the "
"document file when the document is saved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:820
msgid "*Stylesheet* –OMNotebook follows the style settings defined in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:819
msgid ""
"stylesheet.xml and the correct style is applied to a cell when the cell "
"is created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:828
msgid "*Automatic Chapter Numbering* – OMNotebook automatically numbers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:823
msgid ""
"different chapter, subchapter, section and other styles. The user can "
"specify which styles should have chapter numbers and which level the "
"style should have. This is done in the stylesheet.xml file. Every style "
"can have a <chapterLevel> tag that specifies the chapter level. Level 0 "
"or no tag at all, means that the style should not have any chapter "
"numbering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:832
msgid "*Scrollarea* – Scrolling through a document can be done by using the"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:831
msgid ""
"mouse wheel. A document can also be scrolled by moving the cell cursor up"
" or down."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:841
msgid "*Syntax highlighter* – The syntax highlighter runs in a separated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:835
msgid ""
"thread which speeds up the loading of large document that contains many "
"Modelica code cells. The syntax highlighter only highlights when letters "
"are added, not when they are removed. The color settings for the "
"different types of keywords are stored in the file modelicacolors.xml. "
"Besides defining the text color and background color of keywords, whether"
" or not the keywords should be bold or/and italic can be defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:849
msgid "*Change indicator* – A star (\\*) will appear behind the filename in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:844
msgid ""
"the title of notebook window if the document has been changed and needs "
"saving. When the user closes a document that has some unsaved change, "
"OMNotebook asks the user if he/she wants to save the document before "
"closing. If the document never has been saved before, the save-as dialog "
"appears so that a filename can be choosen for the new document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:856
msgid "*Update menus* – All menus are constantly updated so that only menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/omnotebook.rst:852
msgid ""
"items that are linked to actions that can be performed on the currently "
"selected cell is enabled. All other menu items will be disabled. When a "
"textcell is selected the Format menu is updated so that it indicates the "
"text settings for the text, in the current cursor position."
msgstr ""

